# Accessibility

## ARIA Labels
- Provide `aria-label` for interactive elements without visible text
- Use `aria-labelledby` and `aria-describedby` for relationships
- All user-facing text (including aria-labels) must come from `content.json`

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
<button aria-label={content.hero.buttons.getInTouch.ariaLabel}>
  {content.hero.buttons.getInTouch.label}
</button>
```

## Semantic HTML
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<section>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, etc.)
- Use proper heading hierarchy (`h1` → `h2` → `h3`)
- Provide proper `role` attributes when needed

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
<section id={SECTIONS.ABOUT} aria-labelledby='about-heading'>
  <h2 id='about-heading'>About</h2>
  {/* content */}
</section>
```

## Keyboard Navigation
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Provide visible focus indicators
- Handle keyboard events appropriately

## Skip Links
- Include "Skip to main content" link for keyboard users
- Make skip links visible on focus

## External Links
- Always include `rel='noopener noreferrer'` for external links
- Use `target='_blank'` for external links

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
<Link href={url} target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>
  External Link
</Link>
```
